Title: Some Properties of Charge-Conjugated Spinors in $D$ dimensions

Authors: M. A. De Andrade

Comments: 6 pages (latex)

Journal-ref: Mod. Phys. Lett. A10 (1995) 961

Spinors for an arbitrary Minkowski space with signature ($t$, $s$) arereassessed in connection with $D$-dimensional free Dirac action. Thepossibility of writing down kinetic and mass terms for charge-conjugatedspinors is discussed in terms of the number of time-like directions of thespace-time.